However, the risk persists.
We have few, even very few cosmonauts that have had nothing and that give birth to healthy offspring after long flights.
"And if they are longer, it poses a danger even during orbital flights," concludes the pilot and cosmonaut, hero of the Soviet Union and hero of Russia, Valeriy Poliakov.
