It therefore seems that the procedures for the survival of companies authorized by Mexican laws are not valid in the country with the starred banner, at the expense of international agreements.
From a practical point of view, the blow to the judgment handed down on 15 June by Judge Harlin Hale of the Court of Bankruptcy for the North District of Texas leaves Mexican companies defenceless in the face of the possibility of embargoing their properties beyond Bravo.
However, the resolution will allow Mexico's leading glass manufacturer to refer the matter to the U.S. Supreme Court based on three inconsistencies.
